veil-browser (separate Chromium fork project)
---------------------------------------------

veil-browser is a Brave-derived Chromium fork. Its license stack:

  - Veil patches modifying MPL-2.0 files: MPL-2.0
  - Veil-original helper sources (veil_persona.cc, etc.): MPL-2.0
  - Brave Browser source: MPL-2.0
  - Chromium source: BSD-3-Clause + various per-file licenses
  - V8: BSD-3-Clause
  - Skia: BSD-3-Clause
  - ICU: ICU License (BSD-style)
  - libwebp, libpng, libjpeg, zlib, brotli, ...: each under their own
    permissive license (MIT/BSD/zlib).

The full third-party notice for veil-browser is generated at build
time from Brave's own about:credits page and shipped inside the
binary at chrome://credits.


Bundled / invoked external programs (not Go modules)
----------------------------------------------------

pasta / passt — GPL-2.0-or-later — https://passt.top/
  Userspace network uplink for the zero-capability engine. veil runs pasta as a
  SEPARATE PROCESS (it does not link pasta), so pasta's GPL does not extend to
  veil. install.sh builds pasta from upstream source; the Docker image bundles a
  built pasta binary, so anyone redistributing that image must make its
  corresponding source available (upstream passt at the commit pinned in
  packaging/docker/Dockerfile, PASST_REF). No pasta source is modified or
  vendored into this repository.

Invoked at runtime as separate processes — provided by the operating system,
NOT distributed by veil (invoking them does not make veil a derivative work):
  tor (BSD-3-Clause), iptables (GPL-2.0), iproute2 (GPL-2.0),
  nss-tools / certutil (MPL-2.0 / GPL / LGPL), util-linux (GPL-2.0 / misc),
  procps (GPL-2.0 / LGPL).


